************** G E N E R A L   I N F O R M A T I O N ************ 7325 1451
                                                                  7325 1451
This evaluated data file is based primarily on the nuclear model  7325 1451
code Talys [kon07], version 1.0.                                  7325 1451
It is part of a large collection of isotopic                      7325 1451
evaluations, all created by running Talys with default input      7325 1451
parameters. This means that the data in this evaluation have not  7325 1451
been tested in detail against individual experimental data for    7325 1451
this isotope, but is only as good as the global quality of Talys  7325 1451
at the present moment. The mutual quality of all individual       7325 1451
evaluations is thus relatively consistent. The same set of        7325 1451
nuclear models is used and, equally important, the same ENDF-6    7325 1451
formatting procedures for each isotope. The resulting data file   7325 1451
provides a complete representation of nuclear data needed for     7325 1451
transport, damage, heating, radioactivity, and shielding          7325 1451
applications over the incident neutron energy range from 1.0E-11  7325 1451
to 20 MeV. A complete set of covariance data is included.         7325 1451
                                                                  7325 1451
All transport data for neutrons, other particles, photons and     7325 1451
residual nuclides are filed using a combination of MF1,2,3,4      7325 1451
and MF6. This includes cross sections, angular distributions,     7325 1451
double-differential spectra, discrete and continuum photon        7325 1451
production cross sections, and residual production (activation)   7325 1451
cross sections. Moreover, isomeric production data are stored in  7325 1451
MF8 and MF10. This evaluation can thus be used as both transport  7325 1451
and activation library. The data file has been created            7325 1451
automatically using the ENDF format generator endl2endf at        7325 1451
Lawrence Livermore National Laboratory.                           7325 1451
